1
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:37,400
ignoring the workers' livelihoods

2
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:40,160
and just driving them all away

3
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:43,200
that would break their hearts

4
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:47,480
And if you try to bring them back later

5
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:52,680
it'll be extremely difficult

6
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:55,880
The reason our Xuan family workers are so loyal

7
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:58,960
is because so many veteran masters

8
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:01,080
have worked with me for decades

9
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:02,680
And those younger workers

10
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:04,760
I trained them all myself, hands-on

11
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:07,040
That's what gives our Xuan family's xuan paper

12
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:09,360
its guarantee of top quality

13
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:12,320
praised by everyone

14
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:14,880
and standing the test of time

15
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:22,480
We can't even sell the stuff anymore

16
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,720
and you're still being so picky?

17
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:26,760
What kind of nonsense is that?

18
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:29,920
These past two years have been rough

19
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:32,800
but we've still got a long road ahead

20
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,400
If we don't fix the problems of these two years

21
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:37,840
the future will only get worse

22
00:02:41,640 --> 00:02:42,520
Dad, look

23
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:44,320
A discussion is just a discussion, right?

24
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:45,240
Mom said it too

25
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:46,480
stick to the matter at hand

26
00:02:46,480 --> 00:02:47,960
focus on the issue, not the person

27
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:49,600
You tell me

28
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:52,560
if we shut things down now

29
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:54,800
halt production for two years

30
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:57,440
the workers are gone, and I'm getting old

31
00:02:59,160 --> 00:03:00,640
Can you take my place?

32
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:07,880
This xuan paper

33
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:10,120
is regulated by the state now

34
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,400
So many wonderful things

35
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:14,400
If I shot a short video, it'd definitely go viral

36
00:03:14,760 --> 00:03:16,480
Next time you've got something this good, take me along

37
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:19,760
Xuan paper takes 108 separate steps to make

38
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:21,000
Stop tapping

39
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:22,800
There's nobody in that livestream

40
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,080
You've clicked tens of thousands of likes

41
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:25,400
It looks suspicious at a glance

42
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:26,440
Says who?

43
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:28,000
There was just one viewer here a moment ago

44
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:29,280
That person just now

45
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:30,480
was me

46
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:34,760
Aunt Xu told me about the fallout after the contest

47
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:36,760
The Xuan family's having a tough time too

48
00:03:37,040 --> 00:03:38,520
Some day, head over to the Xuans'

49
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:40,760
and shoot some footage of Auntie's products

50
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:43,320
and help spruce up her online shop while you're at it

51
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:44,400
Sure thing

52
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:45,960
Isn't that killing two birds with one stone?

53
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:48,040
Leave it to me

54
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:49,520
A truly fine sheet of xuan paper

55
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:20,760
Don't you see what time it is?

56
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:22,160
Still wandering around out there.

57
00:04:22,880 --> 00:04:24,480
I was about to fall asleep.

58
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:28,760
We can't pay the wages now.

59
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:32,320
Everyone's looking a bit off.

60
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:34,760
Did you let everyone know?

61
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:36,400
I did.

62
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:41,360
About the loan Xiao Lin mentioned,

63
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:43,480
go ask her tomorrow.

64
00:04:43,520 --> 00:04:46,440
See if the Xuan family qualifies.

65
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:48,960
I already asked.

66
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:52,640
She said yes, she'd process it soon.

67
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:57,880
So you knew already?

68
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:59,320
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

69
00:05:00,320 --> 00:05:01,920
Why should I have told you sooner?

70
00:05:02,320 --> 00:05:03,760
I wanted to see you sweat.

71
00:05:08,960 --> 00:05:10,840
Of course I'm worried!

72
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,160
No money to pay wages

73
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:15,520
means the factory can't go on.

74
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:17,280
After all, I'm still the head

75
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:18,640
of this household.

76
00:05:18,760 --> 00:05:19,680
Of course you are.

77
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:23,560
Whenever big or hard things come up,

78
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:27,040
you're the one shouldering it all.

79
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:28,760
Good that you know.

80
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:32,320
Actually, what's worrying me is Xuan Liao.

81
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:37,920
Why worry about him?

82
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:40,160
How can I not worry?

83
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:44,560
We can't let Xuan Liao keep drifting.

84
00:05:44,840 --> 00:05:46,560
Go right now and get Xuan Liao

85
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:47,800
out of bed.

86
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:49,760
Now?

87
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:52,480
Yes.

88
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:54,320
Right now.

89
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:56,080
Hurry up.

90
00:05:56,840 --> 00:05:57,680
Come on, Mom.

91
00:05:58,280 --> 00:05:59,920
It's the middle of the night. What's gotten into him?

92
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:00,920
Can't this wait till morning?

93
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:01,880
Exactly.

94
00:06:03,440 --> 00:06:04,160
Seriously, Mom.

95
00:06:04,720 --> 00:06:05,840
It's nothing major, right?

96
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:07,080
I have no idea.

97
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:09,400
Hurry, hurry.

98
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:10,160
He's waiting for you.

99
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:17,040
Dad.

100
00:06:17,840 --> 00:06:18,560
Sit here.

101
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:23,240
You two, father and son,

102
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:24,680
talk things out calmly.

103
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,320
Stick to the matter at hand.

104
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:27,400
Don't let emotions get in the way.

105
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:36,640
As for you, you're not young anymore.

106
00:06:37,280 --> 00:06:40,880
What you'll do, how you'll do it,

107
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:43,800
you need a long-term plan.

108
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:45,360
You can't just

109
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:48,160
stay cooped up in your room all day.

110
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:50,800
You've turned yourself into some embroidery girl.

111
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:51,920
How can that work?

112
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:55,160
I knew it.

113
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:57,160
You can never say anything nice.

114
00:06:57,920 --> 00:06:58,720
Dad.

115
00:06:58,800 --> 00:06:59,720
When I came back,

116
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:02,560
didn't we lay down some rules?

117
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:04,600
I don't bother you,

118
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:06,920
and you stay out of my business.

119
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:09,360
We each mind our own, right?

120
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:10,400
And it's been proven

121
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:12,480
we get along just fine that way.

122
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:16,160
Now the family is in trouble,

123
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:20,160
we should all stick together,

124
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:21,480
think as one,

125
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:22,800
pull in the same direction.

126
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,480
There's nothing wrong with that, right?

127
00:07:25,160 --> 00:07:26,240
Not entirely right.

128
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:27,840
This factory

129
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:29,600
is run by you and Mom.

130
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:31,480
Honestly, it has nothing to do with me.

131
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:32,520
And I don't want to get involved.

132
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:35,160
You're the 36th-generation heir of the Xuan family!

133
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:37,800
It's not the imperial throne.

134
00:07:37,880 --> 00:07:39,520
Why insist on passing it down?

135
00:07:40,240 --> 00:07:41,240
What did you say?

136
00:07:41,640 --> 00:07:43,240
Say that to me again!

137
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:45,920
Good words aren't repeated twice.

138
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:53,360
Here's what you do.

139
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:56,040
Tomorrow, go to the drying yard.

140
00:07:56,960 --> 00:07:58,600
Wait, did I hear that right?

141
00:07:58,760 --> 00:07:59,560
You want me to...

142
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:01,240
What am I supposed to do there?

143
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:04,320
The drying yard's piled up with sandalwood bark.

144
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:06,720
Only Master Lin's over there now.

145
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:07,720
He's getting on in years.

146
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:08,960
He can't do much anymore.

147
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:10,560
And hiring someone right now,

148
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:12,120
isn't an option given our situation.

149
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,920
You go help Master Lin out.

150
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:16,360
Turn the stored bark into scorched bark.

151
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:18,040
That way, on materials,

152
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:19,960
we'd save a big chunk, right?

153
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,480
What are you laughing at?

154
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:25,560
I'm laughing at you, Dad.

155
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:27,280
You really see your own son

156
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:28,720
as nothing but cheap labor,

157
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:30,760
worth only three or four grand a month.

158
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:33,360
You'd charge your own family for work?

159
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:35,799
I've gotta weigh the cost-benefit, don't I?

160
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,280
I've done the math for you.

161
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:39,679
It beats staying home.

162
00:08:40,039 --> 00:08:42,720
You lying around at home is worth nothing.

163
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,600
That's not called lying around.

164
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:46,120
Then what would you call it?

165
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:47,800
You lock yourself in your room all day,

166
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:49,240
taking my top-grade Xuan paper

167
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:50,680
to make those toys of yours.

168
00:08:50,680 --> 00:08:51,600
What's the use of that?

169
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:53,280
Toys? What toys?

170
00:08:53,280 --> 00:08:54,560
Of course they're useful.

171
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:55,480
I've told you before,

172
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:57,840
your son makes Xuan paper cultural goods.

173
00:08:57,920 --> 00:09:00,120
Last time I showed you that little notebook.

174
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:01,280
At the auction last year,

175
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:03,040
that notebook went for over two thousand.

176
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:04,480
How could you forget?

177
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:10,880
Speaking of which,

178
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:13,120
there's something I want to discuss with you.

179
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:15,200
When you do business,

180
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:17,720
you've got to stay honest.

181
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:20,400
You operate with integrity.

182
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:22,760
A stack of six-foot pure-bark Xuan paper

183
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:24,960
only sells for two thousand.

184
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:26,160
That little notebook of yours,

185
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:27,480
no bigger than a palm,

186
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:28,720
also sells for two thousand?

187
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:29,720
Does that seem right?

188
00:09:29,920 --> 00:09:31,160
Buying and selling,

189
00:09:31,280 --> 00:09:32,720
there's a buyer and a seller, right?

190
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:34,720
They have a demand, I supply it.

191
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:36,360
I'm not forcing anyone to buy.

192
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:38,360
What matters in business is...

193
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:39,040
Is what?

194
00:09:39,040 --> 00:09:40,400
Integrity in business.

195
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:42,480
No matter what we do,

196
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:44,240
we've gotta have a conscience.

197
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:46,720
Hand on your heart, hand on your heart.

198
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:47,920
Forget it, forget it. Let's drop it.

199
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:48,800
Dad, we're done talking.

200
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:49,560
No more arguing.

201
00:09:49,560 --> 00:09:51,480
Mom, don't bother talking to Dad either.

202
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:53,920
You can't get through to him anyway, right?

203
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:55,960
It's so late, just go to bed.

204
00:09:56,040 --> 00:09:56,960
Take care of yourselves.

205
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:57,600
No, no, no.

206
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:58,920
Son, son, son.

207
00:09:58,920 --> 00:10:00,000
Come, come, sit, sit.

208
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:01,280
Sit.

209
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:03,080
Didn't I already tell you?

210
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:04,400
Just ignore him.

211
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:08,040
All he knows in life is scooping paper.

212
00:10:09,680 --> 00:10:10,680
Whatever you want to do,

213
00:10:10,680 --> 00:10:11,560
just tell Mom.

214
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:12,760
Mom supports you.

215
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:14,320
Once you've made something of yourself,

216
00:10:14,520 --> 00:10:15,680
we'll show him.

217
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:19,800
He's still sick anyway, isn't he?

218
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:25,840
Dad.

219
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:31,120
I won't be an eyesore at home anymore.

220
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:32,360
First thing tomorrow,

221
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:33,560
I'll head to the drying yard.

222
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:35,760
I'll do as you wish.

223
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:09,720
Uncle Lin

224
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:11,200
Uncle Lin

225
00:11:12,680 --> 00:11:13,920
I came to see you

226
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:15,440
Yeah, right

227
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:17,560
You got banished here

228
00:11:17,560 --> 00:11:19,360
and now you say you came to visit me?

229
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:22,160
Uncle Lin

230
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:24,800
See if there's any work here

231
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:25,760
and put me to it

232
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:26,640
Forget it

233
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,040
You

234
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:31,800
just eat and sleep as you please

235
00:11:31,920 --> 00:11:32,800
Here

236
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:35,000
there's no one else, just us two

237
00:11:35,160 --> 00:11:36,760
Once your dad cools down

238
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:37,920
hurry back home

239
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:39,280
Have some fun while you can

240
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:40,680
Wait

241
00:11:48,160 --> 00:11:48,760
Uncle Lin

242
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:49,560
Take it slow

243
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,040
Come down slowly

244
00:11:51,160 --> 00:11:51,920
Okay, okay

245
00:11:53,560 --> 00:11:54,560
Easy now

246
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:58,000
Oh my goodness

247
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,280
What are you doing?

248
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:00,160
Taking your picture

249
00:12:00,160 --> 00:12:01,280
No, no, don't take mine

250
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:02,560
Why take pictures of me?

251
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:03,320
You look good

252
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:04,400
What? What looks good?

253
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:05,800
I'm an old man now

254
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:08,800
Nobody wants to see this face

255
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:10,000
So handsome

256
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:11,480
So handsome

257
00:12:11,720 --> 00:12:13,240
Oh my goodness

258
00:12:13,320 --> 00:12:15,920
You should've seen me when I was young

259
00:12:15,920 --> 00:12:17,160
Now that was handsome

260
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:18,440
Behind me

261
00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:20,520
were crowds of girls with long braids

262
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:21,480
Uncle Lin

263
00:12:21,560 --> 00:12:22,480
Strike a couple more poses

264
00:12:22,600 --> 00:12:23,360
Come on, come on

265
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:25,200
Let me style you a bit

266
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:25,520
Okay

267
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:26,200
Alright then

268
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:27,480
How's this?

269
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:28,320
So gorgeous

270
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:29,800
Uncle Lin

271
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:31,120
What are you up to?

272
00:13:31,240 --> 00:13:32,560
Well, you're here now.

273
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:35,840
I'm fixing you some radish.

274
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:37,720
Don't bother, stop it.

275
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:38,760
I've already arranged it.

276
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:39,760
There's food being delivered.

277
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:42,360
Delivered?

278
00:13:42,880 --> 00:13:43,720
Takeout.

279
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:45,080
Takeout?

280
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:47,120
Stop, just stop now.

281
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:49,240
Here, here, here.

282
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:50,160
Takeout.

283
00:13:52,280 --> 00:13:53,080
Thanks for your trouble.

284
00:13:53,760 --> 00:13:56,440
You came all the way to see me,

285
00:13:56,960 --> 00:13:58,200
and didn't get to eat my cooking.

286
00:13:58,200 --> 00:14:00,000
Instead, you're treating me.

287
00:14:01,280 --> 00:14:03,840
Honoring you is only right.

288
00:14:04,680 --> 00:14:05,520
Uncle Lin,

289
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:08,040
you've done such hard, exhausting work here,

290
00:14:08,040 --> 00:14:08,760
right?

291
00:14:09,840 --> 00:14:12,000
And you've done it your whole life,

292
00:14:12,120 --> 00:14:13,840
guarding this drying yard for the Xuan family.

293
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:15,520
If not you, then who would I honor?

294
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:18,880
You really are a thoughtful kid.

295
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:21,600
No wonder the Xuan family always succeeds.

296
00:14:22,280 --> 00:14:24,840
You think of me before anything else.

297
00:14:25,680 --> 00:14:27,680
Your grandfather was like that,

298
00:14:27,760 --> 00:14:29,200
your father is like that,

299
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:31,120
and now you're the same too.

300
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:32,720
You're bound to succeed.

301
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:35,280
Uncle Lin, if it's not enough,

302
00:14:35,280 --> 00:14:36,200
there's more right here.

303
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:38,720
And I brought you a bottle of fine liquor.

304
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:40,640
Let me drink one with you.

305
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:45,520
Here.

306
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:53,160
Let me see.

307
00:14:55,280 --> 00:14:57,560
Bottled liquor really does smell great.

308
00:14:58,520 --> 00:14:59,440
Glad you like it.

309
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:04,200
Uncle Lin,

310
00:15:05,160 --> 00:15:06,320
let me ask you something.

311
00:15:07,080 --> 00:15:09,840
How much do my parents pay you a month?

312
00:15:10,560 --> 00:15:14,160
With holiday bonuses and social security,

313
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:16,800
about 70,000 yuan a year.

314
00:15:20,080 --> 00:15:21,800
My parents are really being unfair.

315
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:23,840
This job is hard and exhausting,

316
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:25,080
and they pay you so little.

317
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:26,520
That's way too low.

318
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:29,560
Then how about this:

319
00:15:29,560 --> 00:15:31,080
whenever you take over,

320
00:15:31,560 --> 00:15:32,800
you give me a raise.

321
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:34,520
No need to wait till I take over.

322
00:15:35,080 --> 00:15:35,880
Uncle Lin,

323
00:15:35,920 --> 00:15:37,960
let's work together right now.

324
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:41,200
Not only will I raise your wages,

325
00:15:41,520 --> 00:15:44,080
I'll help you save up some retirement money too.

326
00:15:45,680 --> 00:15:47,320
There's really such a good deal?

327
00:15:47,320 --> 00:15:48,680
Of course there is.

328
00:15:49,080 --> 00:15:49,840
I see.

329
00:15:49,920 --> 00:15:53,280
Starting tomorrow, just follow my plan.

330
00:15:54,320 --> 00:15:55,200
I'll do what you say.

331
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:56,600
Cheers.

332
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:18,400
Zhang Du.

333
00:16:19,560 --> 00:16:20,400
Master.

334
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:21,320
What's all this?

335
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:24,200
Don't you recognize it?

336
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:26,560
Of course I do.

337
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:30,520
Come, Master.

338
00:16:30,520 --> 00:16:32,400
This is the old stone mortar

339
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:34,520
from the workshop on our back hill.

340
00:16:34,920 --> 00:16:35,720
That's right.

341
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:37,320
I hauled it down here.

342
00:16:40,160 --> 00:16:42,800
This thing weighs over 300 pounds.

343
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:44,080
You...

344
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:47,200
Why'd you drag this down?

345
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:50,320
I just felt

346
00:16:50,920 --> 00:16:53,080
this was left by the Xuan ancestors.

347
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:55,920
We can't just leave it out in the wild.

348
00:16:56,680 --> 00:16:57,520
Master.

349
00:16:57,680 --> 00:16:59,840
I wanted to discuss with you,

350
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:03,040
can we go back to using this old stone mortar

351
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:03,800
from now on?

352
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:08,560
The current one's just made of cement.

353
00:17:09,079 --> 00:17:11,319
I think our old stone mortar is better.

354
00:17:13,079 --> 00:17:14,280
Is there really a difference?

355
00:17:15,520 --> 00:17:16,920
Using this old mortar,

356
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:18,720
you can really feel

357
00:17:19,079 --> 00:17:21,319
the heart our ancestors put into papermaking.

358
00:17:21,960 --> 00:17:24,119
There's emotion woven into it.

359
00:17:24,440 --> 00:17:26,079
That's true heritage,

360
00:17:26,319 --> 00:17:27,680
the real ancient method.

361
00:17:37,440 --> 00:17:39,840
Fine, use it if you want.

362
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:40,920
Great, Master!

363
00:17:42,080 --> 00:17:43,200
Get some rest soon.

364
00:17:43,800 --> 00:17:45,400
I'll head back once I clean it up.

365
00:17:46,680 --> 00:17:47,600
Take care, Master.

366
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:48,680
Okay.

367
00:17:58,960 --> 00:17:59,880
Thank you, Master.

368
00:18:07,360 --> 00:18:09,400
Xuan Family Xuan Paper Mill.

369
00:18:10,520 --> 00:18:11,320
Auntie.

370
00:18:11,320 --> 00:18:13,560
First off, this name just isn't right.

371
00:18:14,240 --> 00:18:15,480
It's got no internet appeal.

372
00:18:16,520 --> 00:18:17,320
Internet appeal?

373
00:18:17,880 --> 00:18:19,160
Let me change it for you.

374
00:18:26,080 --> 00:18:29,600
Prettiest Xuan Paper Mill Boss Lady.

375
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:30,520
No, no, no.

376
00:18:30,560 --> 00:18:31,840
You can't write it like that.

377
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:33,280
Why not, Auntie?

378
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:34,800
Aren't you the boss lady of the paper mill?

379
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:35,320
Yes.

380
00:18:35,320 --> 00:18:35,800
Right.

381
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:36,800
And aren't you pretty?

382
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:37,880
That was when I was young.

383
00:18:38,240 --> 00:18:39,560
Still, you can't write it like that.

384
00:18:39,560 --> 00:18:40,080
You're pretty.

385
00:18:40,080 --> 00:18:40,720
Really, you can't write that.

386
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:41,880
This is exactly how we should write it.

387
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:44,800
This...

388
00:18:45,080 --> 00:18:46,800
Now look at this description.

389
00:18:47,280 --> 00:18:50,160
Millennial Xuan paper, passed down for a thousand years.

390
00:18:51,240 --> 00:18:52,320
Honestly,

391
00:18:52,360 --> 00:18:55,080
people nowadays don't care how long it's been around.

392
00:18:55,280 --> 00:18:56,560
Let me spruce it up for you.

393
00:18:56,800 --> 00:18:57,640
Okay, okay.

394
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:00,800
Take a look.

395
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:02,320
"Paper used by emperors."

396
00:19:03,360 --> 00:19:04,560
Now that's accurate.

397
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:06,640
Several generations of emperors

398
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:08,600
have all used Xuan family paper.

399
00:19:09,680 --> 00:19:10,480
That's right.

400
00:19:11,080 --> 00:19:12,560
You can say whatever you want,

401
00:19:12,720 --> 00:19:14,360
just don't lie.

402
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:15,560
Uncle Xuan.

403
00:19:15,560 --> 00:19:17,120
Especially for business people.

404
00:19:17,560 --> 00:19:18,440
Don't worry, Uncle Xuan.

405
00:19:18,440 --> 00:19:20,560
Taozi wouldn't make stuff up.

406
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:21,640
Come, sit here.

407
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:22,160
No, no, no.

408
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:22,880
I write based on facts.

409
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:24,160
Lin Yiran, sit, sit.

410
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:25,040
I'll just sit here.

411
00:19:25,480 --> 00:19:27,040
Alright, alright, ignore him.

412
00:19:27,560 --> 00:19:29,600
If you've got nothing to do, go rest.

413
00:19:29,800 --> 00:19:31,000
These kids are helping me

414
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,120
with some online stuff.

415
00:19:32,120 --> 00:19:33,720
Look at you nitpicking.

416
00:19:33,720 --> 00:19:34,440
Sit, sit, sit.

417
00:19:36,160 --> 00:19:37,640
I don't care what other families do,

418
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:39,160
but when it comes to the Xuan family,

419
00:19:40,520 --> 00:19:41,520
no way.

420
00:19:41,840 --> 00:19:44,280
The Xuan family is different from others.

421
00:19:45,240 --> 00:19:46,160
Yeah, you're different alright.

422
00:19:47,320 --> 00:19:48,360
Dead duck,

423
00:19:48,360 --> 00:19:49,040
still talking tough.

424
00:19:53,360 --> 00:19:54,160
Taozi

425
00:19:54,360 --> 00:19:55,720
Add one more line to your bio

426
00:19:56,120 --> 00:19:59,280
Say "35th-generation heir of the Xuan family"

427
00:19:59,280 --> 00:20:00,720
"Only makes authentic Xuan paper"

428
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:01,800
Okay

429
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:02,800
See? See?

430
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:05,080
Lin Yiran here, now she talks sense

431
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:06,640
You hear that?

432
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:08,320
Whenever it comes to paper

433
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:10,480
He treats it like it's everything

434
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:12,520
His back's already in that shape

435
00:20:12,520 --> 00:20:14,080
And he still wants to scoop paper

436
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:15,880
And Xuan Yi here won't even lend a hand

437
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:19,320
He banished him to the drying yard

438
00:20:19,560 --> 00:20:21,600
Look at that scrawny build of his

439
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:23,280
Can he handle such heavy work?

440
00:20:24,720 --> 00:20:26,080
What's the big deal?

441
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:28,800
Look at Zhang Du

442
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:31,080
It's so late and he's still working

443
00:20:31,080 --> 00:20:32,880
Like Zhang Du's work isn't heavy?

444
00:20:33,320 --> 00:20:35,080
I'm not saying Zhang Du is bad

445
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:36,800
People are just different

446
00:20:37,080 --> 00:20:40,040
Your son has his own mind and ideas

447
00:20:40,040 --> 00:20:41,800
You should respect that

448
00:20:41,800 --> 00:20:42,720
Okay, Uncle, Auntie

449
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:43,800
Let's stop arguing

450
00:20:43,840 --> 00:20:45,600
Since Xuan Yi already went over there

451
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:46,600
Just let him toughen up a bit

452
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:47,320
Right?

453
00:20:47,320 --> 00:20:48,880
Miss Lin, you have no idea

454
00:20:48,880 --> 00:20:51,560
How bitter and exhausting drying-yard work is

455
00:20:51,560 --> 00:20:53,720
A little hardship is nothing

456
00:20:53,800 --> 00:20:56,080
The hardships the two of us endured when young

457
00:20:56,640 --> 00:20:57,960
Were those few?

458
00:20:58,400 --> 00:21:02,120
For young folks, hardship is a blessing

459
00:21:03,760 --> 00:21:04,640
I think so too

460
00:21:04,640 --> 00:21:05,560
Young people, you know

461
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:07,360
A bit more hardship does no harm

462
00:21:07,360 --> 00:21:08,800
Right, we suffered our share

463
00:21:09,280 --> 00:21:09,880
Alright, Auntie

464
00:21:09,880 --> 00:21:11,040
Let's keep editing, keep editing

465
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:12,000
Just ignore him, ignore him

466
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:12,760
Uncle Lin

467
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:14,280
Uncle Lin

468
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:17,120
Tell the workers

469
00:21:17,360 --> 00:21:19,560
To slow their steps down a bit

470
00:21:20,040 --> 00:21:21,160
Okay, okay, okay

471
00:21:21,560 --> 00:21:23,080
Slow down your movements

472
00:21:23,560 --> 00:21:24,640
Plant your feet firmly

473
00:21:24,640 --> 00:21:27,000
Every step must land solidly

474
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:29,520
Tense up your muscles

475
00:21:29,800 --> 00:21:31,080
Muscles, muscles

476
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:32,880
Carrying a load takes muscle

477
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:35,800
That's the only way the texture comes through

478
00:21:36,760 --> 00:21:38,800
Muscles look great on camera

479
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:40,880
Right, look at him, he's great

480
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:42,320
He's got a nice stride going

481
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:54,600
Folks.

482
00:21:54,640 --> 00:21:55,560
Here for the photo shoot?

483
00:21:56,320 --> 00:21:58,040
We saw it recommended online as a hot spot.

484
00:21:58,040 --> 00:21:59,320
Wait, you actually charge for this?

485
00:21:59,320 --> 00:22:01,080
Take a look at where you are.

486
00:22:01,480 --> 00:22:04,280
This is a thousand-year Xuan paper family.

487
00:22:04,280 --> 00:22:06,160
The Xuan family's century-old drying field.

488
00:22:06,320 --> 00:22:07,960
Stand up on top of that,

489
00:22:08,040 --> 00:22:10,560
surrounded by green hills and clear waters.

490
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:11,800
One snap of the shutter,

491
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:12,760
with you standing in the middle,

492
00:22:12,760 --> 00:22:14,400
and you'll look like a fairy descended from heaven.

493
00:22:14,720 --> 00:22:15,520
All right then.

494
00:22:15,640 --> 00:22:16,640
180 per session.

495
00:22:18,160 --> 00:22:19,240
Day session, 180.

496
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:20,800
Morning session, 288.

497
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:22,680
And sunset session, 388.

498
00:22:22,680 --> 00:22:24,120
You break it down like that?

499
00:22:25,480 --> 00:22:28,000
A pro, I see, so I won't insult you.

500
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:29,280
Let me tell you,

501
00:22:29,280 --> 00:22:30,840
today's sunset session

502
00:22:30,840 --> 00:22:33,800
has been booked by several big photography forums.

503
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:35,280
They're all rushing to get their shots.

504
00:22:36,040 --> 00:22:36,960
How about this:

505
00:22:37,480 --> 00:22:40,000
I'll give you a group discount.

506
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:41,600
On top of 20% off,

507
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:44,440
post a video and pics on three social platforms,

508
00:22:44,440 --> 00:22:45,160
and I'll knock off another 20.

509
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:45,880
How's that sound?

510
00:22:46,320 --> 00:22:47,240
What do you think?

511
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:47,880
Works for me.

512
00:22:47,880 --> 00:22:49,200
Let's just do that then.

513
00:22:50,120 --> 00:22:51,200
Uncle Lin.

514
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:54,240
This session's over.

515
00:22:54,880 --> 00:22:55,720
Time for a break.

516
00:22:55,880 --> 00:22:56,720
Okay.

517
00:22:57,280 --> 00:22:58,600
Break time, break time!

518
00:22:58,800 --> 00:22:59,840
Put down whatever you're doing.

519
00:22:59,840 --> 00:23:00,280
Take a break.

520
00:23:00,280 --> 00:23:01,480
Let's head down, come on down.

521
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:03,400
Sit, sit.

522
00:23:05,280 --> 00:23:06,080
You tired?

523
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:07,280
Not too bad.

524
00:23:07,280 --> 00:23:08,160
Really?

525
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:10,720
Way easier than before.

526
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:13,760
Here, try this.

527
00:23:16,440 --> 00:23:17,000
Come on.

528
00:23:17,960 --> 00:23:18,520
Give it a taste.

529
00:23:21,680 --> 00:23:22,480
Good, right?

530
00:23:22,480 --> 00:23:25,480
Oh my, delicious, delicious!

531
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,240
What about those folks up on the hill?

532
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:32,280
They're up there sunbathing with me.

533
00:23:32,560 --> 00:23:33,520
What for?

534
00:23:34,480 --> 00:23:35,560
For the photos, of course.

535
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:38,720
Uncle Lin.

536
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:40,280
I did the math.

537
00:23:40,480 --> 00:23:41,760
Today we made

538
00:23:41,760 --> 00:23:43,600
a total of 3,888.

539
00:23:45,760 --> 00:23:47,200
Oh my goodness!

540
00:23:48,080 --> 00:23:48,920
How much?

541
00:23:49,760 --> 00:23:51,000
3,888.

542
00:23:51,480 --> 00:23:52,480
That much?

543
00:23:53,040 --> 00:23:53,840
Is that a lot?

544
00:23:54,320 --> 00:23:56,040
I'm estimating

545
00:23:56,080 --> 00:23:57,520
I can push monthly revenue

546
00:23:57,520 --> 00:23:59,120
to around 200,000.

547
00:23:59,280 --> 00:24:01,280
Bet you it'll double in two months.

548
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:02,920
200,000?

549
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:06,960
Uncle Lin.

550
00:24:08,280 --> 00:24:10,080
This 1,000 is for you.

551
00:24:10,080 --> 00:24:10,600
No, no.

552
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:11,960
Way too much, way too much.

553
00:24:11,960 --> 00:24:12,480
It's not too much.

554
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:13,120
That's really too much.

555
00:24:13,120 --> 00:24:13,680
Take it, take it, take it.

556
00:24:13,680 --> 00:24:14,320
Too much, too much.

557
00:24:14,320 --> 00:24:15,080
Just take it.

558
00:24:16,560 --> 00:24:18,520
I said I'd give you a raise.

559
00:24:18,520 --> 00:24:20,520
Gotta set some aside for your retirement too.

560
00:24:23,680 --> 00:24:26,280
You're such a good kid, such a good kid.

561
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:28,960
But still,

562
00:24:29,800 --> 00:24:31,520
something's bugging me.

563
00:24:31,520 --> 00:24:32,280
What is it?

564
00:24:32,520 --> 00:24:35,280
Who's gonna do the work up there?

565
00:24:35,520 --> 00:24:37,240
Don't worry, I've got it covered.

566
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:41,040
Here they come now.

567
00:24:42,680 --> 00:24:43,520
Over here, over here, over here!

568
00:24:48,840 --> 00:24:49,640
Boss Xuan

569
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:51,360
I've got everyone arranged

570
00:24:51,360 --> 00:24:52,120
Ten workers

571
00:24:52,120 --> 00:24:53,600
Two hundred per person per day

572
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:54,600
Guaranteed to finish today

573
00:24:54,760 --> 00:24:57,200
Drive the truck over to that workshop

574
00:24:57,880 --> 00:24:58,800
In a bit

575
00:24:58,920 --> 00:25:01,040
Wait for Master Lin to assign your work

576
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:02,000
Got it

577
00:25:02,320 --> 00:25:03,240
Thanks for your hard work

578
00:25:03,960 --> 00:25:06,520
You mean let them do the work?

579
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:10,800
Nice! You've got a sharp mind

580
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:12,960
Way better than your dad

581
00:25:14,160 --> 00:25:15,920
My dad's just stubborn as a mule

582
00:25:16,320 --> 00:25:17,680
Only sticks to his rigid principles

583
00:25:18,200 --> 00:25:20,000
Uncle Lin, let's talk sense here

584
00:25:20,400 --> 00:25:22,720
Money's money, no matter how you make it, right?

585
00:25:23,320 --> 00:25:26,560
Why grind yourself to death for it?

586
00:25:26,560 --> 00:25:28,160
Can't we do something easier

587
00:25:28,520 --> 00:25:29,520
and earn bigger money?

588
00:25:29,520 --> 00:25:30,480
Your dad, well...

589
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:33,760
The way your dad lives and works

590
00:25:34,920 --> 00:25:36,000
he just follows

591
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:38,160
the principles passed down by our ancestors

592
00:25:38,160 --> 00:25:38,960
Exactly

593
00:25:41,280 --> 00:25:44,000
The ancestors didn't have today's conditions

594
00:25:44,160 --> 00:25:45,520
If they did

595
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:47,760
would it even be my turn to do this?

596
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:49,520
You've got a point there

597
00:25:50,320 --> 00:25:51,200
I mean, really

598
00:25:52,160 --> 00:25:53,720
who has a grudge against money?

599
00:25:53,720 --> 00:25:55,000
Exactly, Uncle Lin

600
00:25:55,840 --> 00:25:58,440
Uncle Lin, let's agree on this

601
00:25:59,320 --> 00:26:00,280
About this matter

602
00:26:00,600 --> 00:26:03,680
Just between you and me, nobody else

603
00:26:03,800 --> 00:26:06,040
Let them sweat over scooping the paper

604
00:26:06,160 --> 00:26:09,040
while we sit here counting cash

605
00:26:09,480 --> 00:26:12,200
You mean we can't let word get out?

606
00:26:13,760 --> 00:26:14,680
Keep it quiet

607
00:26:14,960 --> 00:26:15,760
Keep it quiet

608
00:26:15,760 --> 00:26:16,400
Alright

609
00:26:22,920 --> 00:26:23,720
Feels great!

610
00:26:23,760 --> 00:26:25,080
Haven't worked like this in ages

611
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:26,920
Director Liao

612
00:26:27,080 --> 00:26:28,600
You're really impressive

613
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:31,480
Me, I come from farming stock too

614
00:26:31,560 --> 00:26:34,760
Grew up poor, in the fields by age eight

615
00:26:35,520 --> 00:26:36,320
Lin Yiran

616
00:26:36,560 --> 00:26:37,400
Come over here

617
00:26:39,920 --> 00:26:40,760
Take a look

618
00:26:41,720 --> 00:26:44,200
This is what we use to make Xuan paper

619
00:26:44,200 --> 00:26:45,280
sandy-field rice straw

620
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:48,040
Look how long these sandy-field rice stalks are

621
00:26:48,520 --> 00:26:51,080
The fibers are strong

622
00:26:51,080 --> 00:26:52,320
and yield high pulp content

623
00:26:52,320 --> 00:26:55,280
Only our local sandy soil and mountain spring water

624
00:26:55,520 --> 00:26:57,960
can grow rice this fine

625
00:26:58,080 --> 00:27:00,760
Foreigners took it back and tried to replicate it

626
00:27:00,960 --> 00:27:04,480
A tiny difference led to vastly different results

627
00:27:05,200 --> 00:27:06,000
So that's why

628
00:27:06,280 --> 00:27:07,920
only Xuan paper from our Jing County

629
00:27:07,920 --> 00:27:09,400
qualifies as world intangible heritage

630
00:27:10,240 --> 00:27:11,520
That's true enough

631
00:27:11,560 --> 00:27:13,520
But it's not quite accurate

632
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:16,000
Come, everyone listen up

633
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:19,160
to expert Director Liao's textbook answer

634
00:27:19,160 --> 00:27:20,600
Yeah, tell us about it

635
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:23,280
Alright, I'll say a few words

636
00:27:26,240 --> 00:27:27,040
Comrades

637
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:32,240
Xuan paper, as a geographically protected product

638
00:27:32,520 --> 00:27:34,760
is clearly defined by national standards as follows

639
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:39,160
Only paper made from materials produced in Jing County, Anhui

640
00:27:39,480 --> 00:27:41,080
and surrounding areas

641
00:27:41,320 --> 00:27:43,920
green sandalwood bark and sandy-field rice straw

642
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:46,400
crafted within Jing County

643
00:27:47,040 --> 00:27:53,000
using Jing County's unique spring water and traditional methods

644
00:27:53,240 --> 00:27:54,840
finely produced into paper

645
00:27:55,200 --> 00:27:58,000
can truly be called Xuan paper

646
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:00,520
Bravo!

647
00:28:00,520 --> 00:28:01,240
Bravo!

648
00:28:01,240 --> 00:28:01,960
Well said!

649
00:28:01,960 --> 00:28:03,240
Great, great

650
00:28:03,320 --> 00:28:04,160
Comrades

651
00:28:04,680 --> 00:28:06,000
Let's put in some extra effort

652
00:28:06,080 --> 00:28:07,760
and finish this whole patch

653
00:28:07,760 --> 00:28:09,480
Yeah, come on, let's go!

654
00:28:10,120 --> 00:28:10,720
I mean, really

655
00:28:11,560 --> 00:28:13,280
you all came to help me work

656
00:28:13,840 --> 00:28:16,040
my heart, my heart is just...

657
00:28:16,040 --> 00:28:18,320
Granny, your children and grandkids aren't around

658
00:28:18,440 --> 00:28:19,800
so we're all your family now

659
00:28:19,800 --> 00:28:22,320
For anything big or small, just call on us

660
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:25,200
But I don't even know how to thank you all

661
00:28:25,480 --> 00:28:26,840
Thanking us is easy

662
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:28,720
You all know mountain folk songs

663
00:28:28,920 --> 00:28:29,920
Sing us a couple verses

664
00:28:29,920 --> 00:28:31,440
and we'll work with more energy

665
00:28:32,440 --> 00:28:33,560
Alright, alright

666
00:28:35,040 --> 00:28:38,880
Calling my dear, listen close now

667
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:42,160
Listen close now

668
00:29:02,440 --> 00:29:04,760
Today, Director Liao didn't seem so bad after all.

669
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:06,760
He's not bad, just pedantic.

670
00:29:07,200 --> 00:29:08,400
What does "pedantic" mean?

671
00:29:08,720 --> 00:29:10,760
Think about it, he's pushing fifty,

672
00:29:10,760 --> 00:29:13,200
yet nitpicks everything and offends people.

673
00:29:13,200 --> 00:29:15,960
He talks endlessly about work, full of opinions.

674
00:29:16,160 --> 00:29:18,000
But give him real responsibility, he can't handle it.

675
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:19,600
What leader wouldn't get a headache?

676
00:29:21,240 --> 00:29:22,280
Hold on, hold on a second.

677
00:29:23,760 --> 00:29:26,240
Isn't the Xuan family's drying field on the hill nearby?

678
00:29:27,440 --> 00:29:28,320
Why are we going there?

679
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:31,920
The Xuans are using the company for a loan.

680
00:29:31,920 --> 00:29:33,320
Xuan Yi is one of the shareholders.

681
00:29:33,600 --> 00:29:34,920
I need him to sign something.

682
00:29:35,560 --> 00:29:36,760
Sure, let's check it out.

683
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:39,440
I really want to see this paper-heir rich kid

684
00:29:39,440 --> 00:29:41,040
roughing it out at hard labor.

685
00:29:41,800 --> 00:29:42,800
Let's buy something.

686
00:29:42,800 --> 00:29:43,920
Just as a little gesture.

687
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:47,280
Since when did you become so caring?

688
00:29:47,840 --> 00:29:49,960
Not me, it's for his mom.

689
00:29:50,280 --> 00:29:51,320
Wait for me a sec.

690
00:29:51,840 --> 00:29:52,840
Take it easy.

691
00:29:52,840 --> 00:29:53,560
Okay.

692
00:29:58,600 --> 00:29:59,240
Come on.

693
00:29:59,240 --> 00:30:01,800
Attention, my dear photography buffs!

694
00:30:02,400 --> 00:30:04,760
Today, we're holding

695
00:30:05,080 --> 00:30:07,400
the first Drying Field Photography Contest.

696
00:30:07,840 --> 00:30:09,720
The top three winners

697
00:30:10,160 --> 00:30:12,520
will receive, courtesy of us,

698
00:30:12,680 --> 00:30:16,280
yearly, quarterly, or monthly membership cards,

699
00:30:16,840 --> 00:30:19,720
plus barbecue, drinks, and beer.

700
00:30:20,480 --> 00:30:21,040
Come on!

701
00:30:21,240 --> 00:30:24,000
Let's share the good times together

702
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:26,960
and capture these wonderful moments.

703
00:30:27,760 --> 00:30:29,000
How much per person?

704
00:30:31,520 --> 00:30:32,720
We're membership-based.

705
00:30:33,080 --> 00:30:34,560
If a pretty lady's willing to pose,

706
00:30:34,760 --> 00:30:35,560
it's free.

707
00:30:36,240 --> 00:30:37,000
Xuan Yi.

708
00:30:37,440 --> 00:30:38,560
Yiran bought this for you.

709
00:30:39,520 --> 00:30:40,680
You even brought me something?

710
00:30:40,760 --> 00:30:42,240
You're pretty impressive.

711
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:44,840
The drying field's become a viral hotspot overnight.

712
00:30:45,200 --> 00:30:46,680
Just a little side hustle in my spare time.

713
00:30:46,760 --> 00:30:47,560
What would you like to drink?

714
00:30:47,840 --> 00:30:48,640
Juice, please.

715
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:49,760
And you?

716
00:30:49,760 --> 00:30:50,560
Anything's fine.

717
00:30:54,480 --> 00:30:56,480
You've turned this into a photo studio.

718
00:30:56,920 --> 00:30:57,960
Not just photography.

719
00:30:58,400 --> 00:31:00,000
Dance studios, photo-shoot agencies too.

720
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:01,280
And partnerships with kids' programs.

721
00:31:01,320 --> 00:31:02,960
Two days are booked next week.

722
00:31:02,960 --> 00:31:04,200
Children's workshop classes.

723
00:31:04,520 --> 00:31:08,800
From chopping trees to drying pulp.

724
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:09,840
You guys have no idea.

725
00:31:09,840 --> 00:31:10,960
Parents these days,

726
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:12,600
they love making their kids work.

727
00:31:12,600 --> 00:31:14,560
Sign-ups are off the charts.

728
00:31:15,240 --> 00:31:16,960
Your reach is impressively broad,

729
00:31:16,960 --> 00:31:18,320
and the emotional appeal is maxed out.

730
00:31:18,320 --> 00:31:19,520
How'd you come up with this?

731
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:20,960
What I'm doing here is

732
00:31:21,560 --> 00:31:22,840
using limited resources

733
00:31:22,840 --> 00:31:24,480
to create unlimited possibilities.

734
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:28,080
Membership tiers sort users into groups,

735
00:31:28,080 --> 00:31:29,760
then based on each group,

736
00:31:29,760 --> 00:31:31,400
I tailor

737
00:31:31,400 --> 00:31:33,280
fun, engaging activity plans.

738
00:31:33,560 --> 00:31:35,240
Boosts customer loyalty.

739
00:31:35,240 --> 00:31:36,040
What I'm doing

740
00:31:36,040 --> 00:31:38,080
isn't just providing emotional value,

741
00:31:38,480 --> 00:31:39,760
it's also building them

742
00:31:39,760 --> 00:31:41,240
a top-tier social platform.

743
00:31:42,040 --> 00:31:43,960
Your parents were worried about you coming here.

744
00:31:43,960 --> 00:31:45,280
Turns out they worried for nothing.

745
00:31:46,040 --> 00:31:47,800
I've got a brain, I can figure things out.

746
00:31:48,040 --> 00:31:49,280
Why would I

747
00:31:49,560 --> 00:31:51,040
go looking for hardship for no reason?

748
00:31:51,040 --> 00:31:52,440
I'd have to be crazy.

749
00:31:53,240 --> 00:31:53,840
Alright, Taozi.

750
00:31:53,840 --> 00:31:55,200
You delivered it, now hurry along.

751
00:31:55,560 --> 00:31:57,440
Weren't you here to get Xuan Yu's signature?

752
00:31:58,280 --> 00:31:59,760
Right, I almost forgot the main thing.

753
00:32:01,480 --> 00:32:02,280
Here.

754
00:32:03,160 --> 00:32:05,400
Your parents are applying for an interest-free loan.

755
00:32:05,400 --> 00:32:06,320
You're a shareholder,

756
00:32:06,520 --> 00:32:07,840
so you need to sign.

757
00:32:09,440 --> 00:32:10,440
Interest-free loan?

758
00:32:11,240 --> 00:32:13,320
Look, I'll admit you're talented.

759
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:15,000
Maybe I'm overstepping,

760
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:16,520
but I still want to advise you.

761
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:19,280
Your parents running the family business

762
00:32:19,280 --> 00:32:20,480
isn't easy at all.

763
00:32:20,920 --> 00:32:22,840
Honestly, I worry for them.

764
00:32:22,960 --> 00:32:24,920
But as their son,

765
00:32:24,920 --> 00:32:27,560
I think you have responsibilities to shoulder.

766
00:32:27,560 --> 00:32:28,400
Your family carries

767
00:32:28,400 --> 00:32:30,440
the duty of national heritage preservation.

768
00:32:30,760 --> 00:32:32,160
That's what they really want to see.

769
00:32:32,160 --> 00:32:32,800
Hold on.

770
00:32:33,400 --> 00:32:35,160
You're telling me what heritage means?

771
00:32:35,760 --> 00:32:38,240
Hauling loads up the mountain, that's heritage?

772
00:32:39,080 --> 00:32:40,040
Even if that were true,

773
00:32:40,040 --> 00:32:41,520
I still need to eat, don't I?

774
00:32:41,680 --> 00:32:44,200
Workers are waiting for their paychecks each month.

775
00:32:44,200 --> 00:32:46,080
Raw materials need to be paid for on time.

776
00:32:46,080 --> 00:32:47,520
Try being a single cent short.

777
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:50,040
You get them an interest-free loan today,

778
00:32:50,440 --> 00:32:52,520
but have you thought about how they'll pay it back?

779
00:32:52,520 --> 00:32:53,800
The collateral on that loan contract

780
00:32:53,800 --> 00:32:55,440
is our family's old house, you know?

781
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:56,520
If things go wrong,

782
00:32:57,520 --> 00:32:59,160
you're digging a pit for them.

783
00:33:09,560 --> 00:33:10,040
Xiao Lin.

784
00:33:10,760 --> 00:33:12,560
I've given you all the documents.

785
00:33:12,800 --> 00:33:14,040
See if there's anything else you need.

786
00:33:14,040 --> 00:33:14,800
Just ask me again.

787
00:33:14,960 --> 00:33:15,240
Okay.

788
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:16,880
Auntie, this afternoon,

789
00:33:16,880 --> 00:33:19,080
I'll take you to handle everything

790
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:19,760
that requires you to be there in person.

791
00:33:19,760 --> 00:33:20,880
Good, good. Come, come.

792
00:33:20,880 --> 00:33:21,400
It's fine.

793
00:33:21,480 --> 00:33:22,240
Let me take a look.

794
00:33:25,520 --> 00:33:27,520
Our Xuan family

795
00:33:28,280 --> 00:33:30,040
has been going through a rough patch lately.

796
00:33:30,720 --> 00:33:32,000
But the Xuan family

797
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:33,680
has weathered plenty of storms.

798
00:33:33,840 --> 00:33:34,760
This is nothing.

799
00:33:35,240 --> 00:33:36,240
You all just focus on the work.

800
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:37,560
As for wages,

801
00:33:38,200 --> 00:33:40,920
I won't shortchange anyone a single cent.

802
00:33:42,760 --> 00:33:43,760
There's something

803
00:33:43,760 --> 00:33:45,440
I've been meaning to say.

804
00:33:45,640 --> 00:33:48,120
The factory really has no orders right now.

805
00:33:48,440 --> 00:33:50,840
Why don't we just take a break for a few days?

806
00:33:51,200 --> 00:33:53,440
After all, we're all old friends here.

807
00:33:53,440 --> 00:33:54,720
We all understand, right?

808
00:33:56,240 --> 00:33:57,960
Understanding is one thing,

809
00:33:58,480 --> 00:34:00,080
but I'm well aware

810
00:34:00,760 --> 00:34:02,280
of everyone's actual situation.

811
00:34:02,720 --> 00:34:05,800
Take Lao Hu and Sulan, for instance.

812
00:34:05,880 --> 00:34:07,160
Their kid's in college,

813
00:34:07,320 --> 00:34:08,560
and that costs money.

814
00:34:08,960 --> 00:34:10,280
Plus, they took out a loan

815
00:34:10,320 --> 00:34:12,159
on their house in the county.

816
00:34:12,440 --> 00:34:15,760
That loan can't be late even by a day.

817
00:34:16,159 --> 00:34:18,280
We're fine. Don't worry about us.

818
00:34:18,520 --> 00:34:19,520
And Lao Ye too.

819
00:34:19,520 --> 00:34:21,719
His wife works as a nanny in Shanghai.

820
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:24,800
All three of them are scraping together money

821
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:28,239
for Magan'er's wedding gift.

822
00:34:28,280 --> 00:34:29,080
I mean,

823
00:34:29,239 --> 00:34:30,320
if there's no work,

824
00:34:30,320 --> 00:34:32,000
how are they supposed to get by?

825
00:34:32,320 --> 00:34:34,199
We won't be going hungry.

826
00:34:34,600 --> 00:34:36,080
Lao Hu and I as a couple,

827
00:34:36,080 --> 00:34:37,600
we can make it work anywhere.

828
00:34:38,239 --> 00:34:40,840
Lao Ye, Xiaoman, and I have already talked it over.

829
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:42,800
We'll find other work for the time being.

830
00:34:43,080 --> 00:34:44,719
Every bit of relief helps, right?

831
00:34:45,040 --> 00:34:46,719
Whenever the Xuan family needs us,

832
00:34:46,719 --> 00:34:48,120
we'll come back right away.

833
00:34:48,159 --> 00:34:48,960
Right, right, right.

834
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:50,600
That's right, Lao Xuan.

835
00:34:50,920 --> 00:34:52,480
Whenever the Xuan family needs us,

836
00:34:52,480 --> 00:34:53,880
that's when we'll come back.

837
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:54,760
No matter

838
00:34:55,560 --> 00:34:56,560
where we go,

839
00:34:57,600 --> 00:34:58,680
we're still part of the Xuan family.

840
00:34:59,400 --> 00:35:00,200
Right, right.

841
00:35:04,160 --> 00:35:05,600
Hearing you all say these things,

842
00:35:07,080 --> 00:35:08,480
it really touches my heart.

843
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:11,160
But it's not that bad yet.

844
00:35:11,480 --> 00:35:14,040
Isn't Xiao Lin helping us get a loan?

845
00:35:14,960 --> 00:35:15,760
Master Xuan,

846
00:35:15,760 --> 00:35:17,600
don't try to tough it out.

847
00:35:18,040 --> 00:35:20,000
You don't need to worry about me.

848
00:35:20,200 --> 00:35:21,280
Get back to work.

849
00:35:22,400 --> 00:35:23,520
Keep on scooping the paper.

850
00:35:24,040 --> 00:35:25,040
If you stop scooping paper,

851
00:35:25,280 --> 00:35:26,800
then we'll really be starving.

852
00:35:28,280 --> 00:35:29,480
Okay, okay.

853
00:35:31,400 --> 00:35:32,120
Master's wife,

854
00:35:32,840 --> 00:35:33,720
You two,

855
00:35:33,840 --> 00:35:36,760
you cleared out the old house for me.

856
00:35:36,760 --> 00:35:38,400
I eat my meals at the factory too.

857
00:35:38,400 --> 00:35:39,360
It doesn't cost much.

858
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:40,680
From now on,

859
00:35:40,680 --> 00:35:42,200
you don't need to pay me wages.

860
00:35:42,520 --> 00:35:45,200
I get to learn the craft from Master here.

861
00:35:45,600 --> 00:35:47,000
You're not charging me tuition.

862
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:48,200
I'm already getting a great deal.

863
00:35:48,840 --> 00:35:49,560
And another thing,

864
00:35:50,640 --> 00:35:52,600
I have 50,000 yuan here.

865
00:35:52,760 --> 00:35:54,240
I want to help you pull it together.

866
00:35:54,400 --> 00:35:54,960
I can't take it.

867
00:35:54,960 --> 00:35:55,360
Please, take it.

868
00:35:55,360 --> 00:35:57,080
Silly child, put it away.

869
00:35:57,080 --> 00:35:58,200
Listen to me.

870
00:35:58,320 --> 00:35:59,800
Letting you stay at our home,

871
00:35:59,840 --> 00:36:01,040
that's something we're happy to do.

872
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:03,520
You just focus on learning the craft.

873
00:36:03,560 --> 00:36:05,320
If you make the paper well,

874
00:36:05,320 --> 00:36:07,560
your master will be happier than anything.

875
00:36:08,400 --> 00:36:09,680
Listen to me, put it away.

876
00:36:09,680 --> 00:36:11,200
Every little bit helps, Master's wife.

877
00:36:11,200 --> 00:36:12,280
No, no.

878
00:36:12,280 --> 00:36:13,000
You remember this.

879
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:15,080
The Xuan family never owes workers money.

880
00:36:15,080 --> 00:36:16,800
And we can't take this money of yours.

881
00:36:16,800 --> 00:36:18,040
Pick it up.

882
00:36:19,280 --> 00:36:20,000
Master,

883
00:36:20,080 --> 00:36:22,600
I know our factory is in trouble.

884
00:36:22,760 --> 00:36:24,680
But I believe if we all pull together,

885
00:36:24,680 --> 00:36:25,640
and tough it out together,

886
00:36:25,640 --> 00:36:27,000
we can definitely get through this.

887
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:27,520
Exactly.

888
00:36:27,520 --> 00:36:28,840
Xuan Liao earns so much,

889
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:30,680
can't he chip in to pay the wages?

890
00:36:30,720 --> 00:36:31,520
Taozi.

891
00:36:31,800 --> 00:36:33,920
Xuan Liao is out there in those mountains alone.

892
00:36:33,920 --> 00:36:35,160
How would he be making money?

893
00:36:35,600 --> 00:36:36,800
Auntie, you don't know.

894
00:36:36,800 --> 00:36:37,440
Xuan Liao,

895
00:36:37,440 --> 00:36:39,760
turned the drying yard into a photo hotspot.

896
00:36:39,840 --> 00:36:40,560
Old Master Lin is the model.

897
00:36:40,560 --> 00:36:40,960
Taozi.

898
00:36:40,960 --> 00:36:42,160
It makes tons of money.

899
00:36:43,200 --> 00:36:44,160
What? What hotspot?

900
00:36:44,560 --> 00:36:46,720
Photography, taking pictures, check-in spots make money.

901
00:36:46,920 --> 00:36:48,600
It actually makes money?

902
00:37:20,560 --> 00:37:21,640
Smile, smile, give us a smile

903
00:37:21,640 --> 00:37:22,800
Let's take a picture

904
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:26,040
Alright, alright

905
00:37:26,160 --> 00:37:27,520
Good, good, good

906
00:37:27,520 --> 00:37:28,960
This is a true working man

907
00:37:28,960 --> 00:37:30,320
Oh my, look at that sweat

908
00:37:42,600 --> 00:37:43,960
Oh my goodness

909
00:37:44,960 --> 00:37:46,600
You little brat

910
00:37:57,880 --> 00:37:59,040
You're still lying around here

911
00:37:59,040 --> 00:37:59,720
Dad, Dad

912
00:38:00,760 --> 00:38:01,560
What are you doing here?

913
00:38:01,560 --> 00:38:02,320
What am I doing here?

914
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:03,520
You, put that stool down first

915
00:38:03,560 --> 00:38:04,280
Put it down, my ass

916
00:38:04,280 --> 00:38:05,280
Don't, don't, don't

917
00:38:05,440 --> 00:38:06,080
Listen

918
00:38:06,080 --> 00:38:06,840
I know you're angry

919
00:38:06,840 --> 00:38:07,680
But, but don't get worked up

920
00:38:07,720 --> 00:38:09,000
Let me explain

921
00:38:09,400 --> 00:38:11,600
Dad, let's talk this out calmly

922
00:38:12,920 --> 00:38:14,200
You're really trying to kill me!

923
00:38:14,200 --> 00:38:14,960
I'll beat you to death

924
00:38:14,960 --> 00:38:15,760
Have you gone crazy?

925
00:38:17,160 --> 00:38:17,520
Where do you think you're going?

926
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:20,600
Take a light beating, flee a heavy one

927
00:38:20,600 --> 00:38:21,560
That's what true filial piety is

928
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:23,400
I don't blame you for not knowing

929
00:38:23,400 --> 00:38:24,120
Uncle Lin

930
00:38:24,440 --> 00:38:25,800
What good will beating me to death do?

931
00:38:25,800 --> 00:38:26,520
Old Xuan

932
00:38:27,400 --> 00:38:28,160
Old Xuan

933
00:38:28,440 --> 00:38:29,080
Old Xuan

934
00:38:29,080 --> 00:38:30,480
Stop filming! Still filming?

935
00:38:30,480 --> 00:38:31,440
No filming the fight

936
00:38:32,120 --> 00:38:33,360
Old Xuan, don't really hit him

937
00:38:33,440 --> 00:38:33,920
Come on now

938
00:38:34,200 --> 00:38:34,680
Old Xuan

939
00:38:34,680 --> 00:38:35,120
Dad, Dad, Dad

940
00:38:35,120 --> 00:38:35,840
Stop hitting me!

941
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:37,560
Stand right there, you brat!

942
00:38:37,800 --> 00:38:38,320
Wait, no

943
00:38:38,880 --> 00:38:39,520
I'll beat you to death

944
00:38:39,520 --> 00:38:40,360
Beating me to death won't help

945
00:38:40,360 --> 00:38:40,680
You little brat

946
00:38:40,680 --> 00:38:41,640
Old Xuan, Old Xuan

947
00:38:41,640 --> 00:38:43,200
You won't really hit him

948
00:38:43,200 --> 00:38:44,120
You wouldn't really hit him

949
00:38:44,120 --> 00:38:45,520
Just scare him a little, that's enough

950
00:38:45,520 --> 00:38:46,200
Uncle Lin

951
00:38:46,200 --> 00:38:47,000
Uncle Lin, save me!

952
00:38:47,240 --> 00:38:48,160
Uncle Lin, Uncle Lin

953
00:38:48,160 --> 00:38:48,720
Stop hitting him, stop

954
00:38:48,720 --> 00:38:49,600
Don't really hit him, don't

955
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:50,560
Old Xuan

956
00:38:51,720 --> 00:38:52,880
Just give him a scare, that's enough

957
00:38:52,880 --> 00:38:53,280
You wouldn't really hit him

958
00:38:53,280 --> 00:38:54,360
Why don't you hit me instead?

959
00:38:57,440 --> 00:38:57,960
No, listen

960
00:38:58,560 --> 00:38:59,520
Let me ask you, Dad

961
00:38:59,920 --> 00:39:01,480
Is it really worth getting this angry?

962
00:39:01,480 --> 00:39:02,640
You'll just make yourself sick

963
00:39:03,280 --> 00:39:03,920
Yes

964
00:39:04,560 --> 00:39:06,640
I dragged Uncle Lin here to make money taking photos

965
00:39:07,240 --> 00:39:08,760
But who am I making the money for?

966
00:39:09,080 --> 00:39:10,440
Isn't it for our family?

967
00:39:10,640 --> 00:39:11,600
In just one week

968
00:39:11,600 --> 00:39:12,720
I made thirty thousand yuan

969
00:39:13,000 --> 00:39:14,960
A month easily brings in over a hundred thousand

970
00:39:15,160 --> 00:39:16,360
How long would you have to scoop paper

971
00:39:16,360 --> 00:39:17,520
to earn that kind of money?

972
00:39:17,520 --> 00:39:18,520
Bullshit!

973
00:39:18,720 --> 00:39:19,720
You're selling out our ancestors

974
00:39:19,720 --> 00:39:21,000
How much do you think that's worth?

975
00:39:21,200 --> 00:39:22,560
No, Uncle Lin, look at this

976
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:23,880
He's dragging the ancestors out again

977
00:39:23,880 --> 00:39:25,800
Can the ancestors pay the workers' wages?

978
00:39:25,840 --> 00:39:26,640
Just answer me this

979
00:39:26,640 --> 00:39:28,400
If the money's in hand, would you take it?

980
00:39:28,400 --> 00:39:29,280
I'm gonna beat you to death!

981
00:39:29,280 --> 00:39:30,280
Old Xuan, Old Xuan, Old Xuan

982
00:39:30,280 --> 00:39:31,000
It's my fault, my fault

983
00:39:31,160 --> 00:39:32,040
Old Xuan, don't be angry

984
00:39:32,120 --> 00:39:34,640
The kid did it all for me

985
00:39:35,080 --> 00:39:36,240
In his heart

986
00:39:36,400 --> 00:39:38,400
the Xuan family legacy means nothing

987
00:39:38,400 --> 00:39:40,520
All he sees is money

988
00:39:40,960 --> 00:39:42,680
But I did the work too

989
00:39:42,920 --> 00:39:44,960
Didn't I dry the bark material?

990
00:39:45,560 --> 00:39:47,080
Look, see for yourself

991
00:39:47,080 --> 00:39:48,360
Fine, let's take a look

992
00:39:53,440 --> 00:39:54,240
Take a look.

993
00:39:54,520 --> 00:39:56,080
This is the bark you dried?

994
00:39:56,440 --> 00:39:58,440
What's the key to drying bark?

995
00:39:58,640 --> 00:40:00,000
Haven't I told you before?

996
00:40:03,360 --> 00:40:04,360
Two pieces shouldn't touch.

997
00:40:05,160 --> 00:40:06,160
Stones shouldn't face the sky.

998
00:40:07,480 --> 00:40:08,640
Damn it.

999
00:40:08,720 --> 00:40:10,040
You actually remembered?

1000
00:40:10,840 --> 00:40:14,400
Airflow and sunlight make good bark.

1001
00:40:14,440 --> 00:40:15,880
What is this you've dried?

1002
00:40:16,600 --> 00:40:17,520
Just look at it.

1003
00:40:18,080 --> 00:40:19,480
It's all rotten.

1004
00:40:19,800 --> 00:40:20,680
Eight months from now,

1005
00:40:20,680 --> 00:40:22,240
this will all be a pile of trash.

1006
00:40:22,240 --> 00:40:23,800
You think you can dry good bark?

1007
00:40:23,840 --> 00:40:24,880
Make good paper?

1008
00:40:28,840 --> 00:40:30,400
Look at this, Old Lin.

1009
00:40:30,720 --> 00:40:32,720
What kind of people did you hire?

1010
00:40:33,280 --> 00:40:35,880
Trampling all over my bark.

1011
00:40:36,080 --> 00:40:37,120
Can't you see?

1012
00:40:38,160 --> 00:40:39,440
Don't step on that!

1013
00:40:40,920 --> 00:40:41,720
Old Lin.

1014
00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:45,040
He doesn't get it, but you do.

1015
00:40:45,040 --> 00:40:45,840
Old Xuan.

1016
00:40:46,320 --> 00:40:47,800
It's my fault. My fault.

1017
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:49,880
Making paper is like being a person.

1018
00:40:50,000 --> 00:40:52,520
108 steps, none can be skipped.

1019
00:40:52,960 --> 00:40:53,840
But you, on the other hand,

1020
00:40:55,120 --> 00:40:56,720
all you see is quick money.

1021
00:40:57,040 --> 00:40:59,160
The Xuan family's reputation

1022
00:40:59,160 --> 00:41:00,680
and a papermaker's conscience,

1023
00:41:00,680 --> 00:41:02,600
you've trampled them all underfoot.

1024
00:41:03,080 --> 00:41:03,880
Now hurry up

1025
00:41:04,120 --> 00:41:05,600
and chase all these people out!

1026
00:41:05,600 --> 00:41:06,800
And in that little courtyard,

1027
00:41:06,800 --> 00:41:08,400
that, that loudspeaker thing,

1028
00:41:08,560 --> 00:41:09,640
get rid of all of it!

1029
00:41:09,920 --> 00:41:10,840
If you don't listen to me,

1030
00:41:11,000 --> 00:41:12,080
I won't let you off.

1031
00:41:15,200 --> 00:41:16,680
Don't, don't be angry, Old Xuan.

1032
00:41:16,680 --> 00:41:18,000
This is all on me.

1033
00:41:27,120 --> 00:41:28,120
What your father said

1034
00:41:29,840 --> 00:41:30,960
makes a lot of sense.

1035
00:41:32,000 --> 00:41:34,000
This is all Uncle Lin's fault.

1036
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:36,080
No.

1037
00:41:37,080 --> 00:41:39,480
Uncle Lin, I'm sorry.

1038
00:41:40,320 --> 00:41:41,400
This isn't your fault.

1039
00:41:42,320 --> 00:41:43,000
It's mine.

1040
00:41:46,640 --> 00:41:48,600
Stop filming. Still filming?

1041
00:41:50,440 --> 00:41:51,200
Remember this.

1042
00:41:52,040 --> 00:41:54,520
First scoop, water close to you.

1043
00:41:55,000 --> 00:41:57,320
Second scoop, water breaks center.

1044
00:41:58,120 --> 00:41:59,520
This feel in the hands,

1045
00:42:00,080 --> 00:42:03,000
and the skill of the heart are subtly linked.

1046
00:42:03,880 --> 00:42:05,680
The feel takes lots of practice.

1047
00:42:05,680 --> 00:42:06,960
And the skill of the heart,

1048
00:42:07,280 --> 00:42:08,080
you have to deeply grasp.

1049
00:42:08,280 --> 00:42:09,400
Understood, Master Ye.

1050
00:42:12,280 --> 00:42:13,360
Your hands are torn up.

1051
00:42:14,920 --> 00:42:15,440
It's nothing.

1052
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:20,480
This paper-scooping trade,

1053
00:42:20,720 --> 00:42:21,600
what it takes

1054
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:24,640
is years and years of slow grind.

1055
00:42:24,720 --> 00:42:26,280
You can't rush it.

1056
00:42:26,640 --> 00:42:27,560
I started late.

1057
00:42:28,400 --> 00:42:30,800
To get good, I have to practice more.

1058
00:42:31,280 --> 00:42:32,040
Master Ye.

1059
00:42:32,520 --> 00:42:35,200
His hands are raw. What ointment works?

1060
00:42:35,320 --> 00:42:36,720
No ointment really helps.

1061
00:42:36,840 --> 00:42:37,800
Try some cortisone.

1062
00:42:38,040 --> 00:42:38,840
Master.

1063
00:42:38,920 --> 00:42:39,720
Let me see.

1064
00:42:43,880 --> 00:42:45,640
Stay out of the water for a couple days.

1065
00:42:45,960 --> 00:42:46,920
He was right just now.

1066
00:42:46,920 --> 00:42:48,320
No ointment really works.

1067
00:42:48,520 --> 00:42:49,880
A few days of rest will do it.

1068
00:42:49,880 --> 00:42:51,080
Okay, thank you, Master.

1069
00:42:52,000 --> 00:42:53,480
What are you doing with that ladder?

1070
00:42:53,480 --> 00:42:55,200
You're old and your back's bad.

1071
00:42:55,200 --> 00:42:56,320
Let the young folks do it.

1072
00:42:57,000 --> 00:42:57,920
Just changing a lightbulb.

1073
00:42:57,920 --> 00:42:58,440
I'm used to it.
